Intro

pseudolandscape <- read.csv("Pseudolandia.csv")

The malaria landscape of Pseudolandia is remarkably similar to the northern part of Bioko Island. This is a map of the 2500 occupied sectors (i.e. 100m \(\times\) 100m) of Pseudolandia. Pseudolandia is not large, it is approximately \(17.6\) km \(\times\) \(7.8\) km. The population density per sector, \(H\), is heterogeneously distributed:

par(mfrow = c(1,2))
hist(pseudolandscape$pop, xlab = expression(H), main = "Pop Den")
hist(log2(1+pseudolandscape$pop), xlab = expression(log[2](H)), main = "log(Pop Dens)")

clrs = cividis(10)
with(pseudolandscape, plot(utmx, utmy, pch = 22, cex=0.73, col= grey(0.8), #col = clrs[(round(1+log2(pop)))], 
                           bg = clrs[(round(1+log2(pop)))]))

points(465000, 408500, cex = 2, bg = clrs[4], pch =22)
text(465100, 408500, "Pop < 11", cex = 1, pos = 4)
points(465000, 409000, cex = 2, bg = clrs[10], pch =22)
text(465100, 409000, "Pop > 362", cex = 1, pos = 4)

Our first task is to estimate the average annual EIR at sector level.
